#Transforming to data

data_gm = gm[['Country', 'region']].drop_duplicates()
data_w_regions = pd.merge(co2, data_gm, left_on='country', right_on='Country', how='inner')
data_w_regions = data_w_regions.drop('Country', axis='columns')
new_co2 = pd.melt(data_w_regions, id_vars=['country', 'region'])
columns = ['country', 'region', 'year', 'co2']
new_co2.columns = columns
data_co2 = new_co2[new_co2['year'].astype('int64') > 1963]
data_co2 = data_co2.sort_values(by=['country', 'year'])
data_co2['year'] = data_co2['year'].astype('int64')
data_g = gm[['Country', 'Year', 'gdp', 'population', 'fertility',
'life']]
data_g.columns = ['country', 'year', 'gdp', 'population', 'fertility',
'life']
data = pd.merge(data_co2, data_g, on=['country', 'year'], how='left')


data = data.dropna()
